        "report": "Analysis complete: 19 review issues cluster into 4 themes. (1) Monolith: model.py contains 5 classes in 1100 lines \u2014 moderate split complexity. (2) Type patterns: string-based type detection in _compat.py and repeated try/except polars imports \u2014 fixable with helper functions. (3) Contract strictness: _result now initialized in __init__, recommend_items already has DeprecationWarning. (4) Cosmetic: abbreviated var names, many init params \u2014 acceptable for internal/private code. Root cause: fast iteration on Rust core left Python wrappers as accumulated convenience code.",
